Campus Involvement: EPIC, TAMID Investment Fund, Alpha Epsilon Pi Fraternity
Comments: Seems very involved in their major and Launch, but doesn't seem to be as involved in the greater Northwestern community. The answers all had a similar tone which was very computer science/start-up focus, so it'd be interesting to see if they could speak to other aspects of NU in the interview. I don’t think I’d be ready to hire them right now, but there was a lot of effort in the application that shows potential, so I think the interview could be beneficial to see if they could elaborate
Majors: Computer Science, Statistics, Minor in Business German

Campus Involvement: Gamma Phi Beta Sorority, Extreme Measures, Triathlon Club, Nous Fe Club, College Democrats
Comments: The application misses some specifics, but they seem to have a wide range of experiences, and they speak of all of them enthusiastically. The application demonstrates a LOT of purple pride- I would LOVE to see them in the interview stage.

Campus Involvement: Resident Assistant, Hospital Volunteering, Student Mentorship program, Sorority
Comments: Seems to have a lot of enthusiasm for NU students but not necessarily NU itself if that makes sense. I worry that this person might be a little too negative, but the rest of the application is strong, so I would count them out yet
Majors: German, Minors in Chemistry and History

Campus Involvement: A&O Productions, Associated Student Government, The Daily Northwestern, Dale Duro Latin Dance Company, Supplies for Dreams
Comments: You can tell that they have clear passions and how found multiple ways to pursue those passions. I’m the tiniest bit worried about how they write about failure, but I don’t think it’s the end all be all. The application itself wasn’t very creative, but that might just be their writing skills so I’d still want to see them in an interview

Campus Involvement: Spectrum Theatre Company, TBD Performance group, University Singers, Seesaw Theatre
Comments: Their answers are very short, and while they’re clear and concise, it doesn’t seem like they spent very long on the application. The answer to the lesson question was particularly weak, as they only spoke about their experience during the polar vortex and didn’t relate it to the rest of the NU experience. I wouldn’t be ready to hire them at this time

Campus Involvement: Sit and Spin Theatre Board, The Blackout, Waa Mu, Scientific Research Workshop, Research Lab Work (not definite), A Capella (not definite)
Comments: Lots of enthusiasm, and you can tell that a lot of effort was put into the application. Makes it clear that they love to be around people. From the application, they seem like they would make a strong tour guide
Majors: Theater, Biological Sciences, Musical Theater Certificate

Campus Involvement: Theatre, Kappa Alpha Theta sorority, Spoon University
Comments: The story in the video itself took a long time to get to the point and had a lot of extraneous details, and it wasn't until the last 10 seconds that I understood what the story was about. Her response to the rebranding question was more of a "how would you change Northwestern" answer, so it felt a little negative, and although that may have been the interpretation of the question, it wasn't spun well. However, the answers to the first two questions were well-written and enthusiastic, so I wouldn't be opposed to seeing her get an interview
Majors: Theater, Minor in French, Acting for the Screen Module, Kaplan Humanities Scholars Program

Campus Involvement: Medill Media Teens, WNUR
Comments: The answers were concise, but although they are involved in a couple of things, they seem to have a very basic understanding of the Northwestern community, and I think they would be a better hire for a later year, because the enthusiasm is there

Campus Involvement: Tufaan, Active Minds, APO
Comments: Answers are not completely spun out, which is a little concerning. The slogan question played off of NU's "rivalry" with U Chicago, which felt a little uncomfortable, and that same question wasn't fleshed out, and the enthusiasm was hesitant; there was enthusiasm in some of the other questions, but this one answer just stuck out most to me

Campus Involvement: Chicago Undergraduate Program, Jewish Theatre Ensemble
Comments: The first answer was well fleshed out and detailed, but the others all had a drastically different tone, and they were significantly shorter and taken less seriously. I think they would be a stronger candidate for a later time, but the video was strong and the story was entertaining so there is potential there, so an interview may be valuable
Majors: Theatre, Possibly Creative Writing, Minor in Psychology, Musical Theatre Certificate

Campus Involvement: Purple Haze, Phi Delta Theta, IM Sports
Comments: The answers to each of the questions weren't very clear and bounced from topic to topic. He speaks a lot about himself and his own experience, but struggle to connect those experiences to the greater Northwestern community, which I would want to see more if he was brought to an interview
Majors: Economics, Performance Studies, Music Theatre Certificate

Campus Involvement: Girl Up, CSA, Northwestern Visual Society
Comments: Most of the answers seemed really strong and enthusiastic, but there were a couple of short snippets that were off-putting like "Didn't NU pay a bunch of money for the freshman class last year to go see that show?" and wanting to only spend a day in the life of a professor to get his books, but this may be more the way their writing comes across, and the rest of it was very strong so an interview may give more insight
Majors: Environmental Science, Comparative Literary Studies, Minor in General Music

Campus Involvement: Delta Tau Delta
Comments: Doesn't list being involved in anything but a fraternity, although mentions in the favorite campus activity that they're part of club track, and the questions don't show much breadth. It also gets really negative when talking about the winter, so I don't know if they'd be ready yet

Campus Involvement: Steam Heat, Kappa Delta Sorority
Comments: She spun her video well, and demonstrated a good sense of humor. The written application definitely shows her passion for community, and not just in her specific extracurriculars. Her general campus awareness isn't the strongest, but I still think she would make a VERY strong tour guide

Campus Involvement: Powder Blue Media, Northwestern Men's Ultimate Team
Comments: Seems very involved in the Garage and their startup, but doesn't seem to be as involved in the greater Northwestern community. The answers were all focused on start-up culture, so similar to other applicants I’ve seen, it'd be interesting to see if they could speak to other aspects of NU in the interview. I don’t think I’d be ready to hire them right now, but there was a lot of NU pride in there so there could be potential
Majors: Journalism, Minors in Entrepreneurship and History, Leadership Certificate

Campus Involvement: Camp Kesem, Evans Scholars, Lurie's Children's Hospital
Comments: I really enjoyed reading this application, and they had GREAT storytelling ability. Their slogan answer was the most creative of the applications that I've read, and they related each of their answers to the greater NU community. If it were only based off of the written application, I'd hire them now

Campus Involvement: Best Buddies, Northwestern's Undergraduate Real Estate Club
Comments: Really makes the most of their campus involvement, and demonstrates a lot of purple pride while keeping a strong emphasis on campus community. Would love to see more of a spark of creativity, but I think that could come in the interview- I think they would be a strong candidate
Majors: Learning and Organizational Change, Minor in Entrepreneurship and/or Philosophy (currently deciding)

Campus Involvement: Lifeguard, Wirtz Box Office, Seesaw
Comments: Video was really thoughtful and connected back to  NU and played out very well. Demonstrates a lot of energy and enthusiasm, but felt solidly a "4" instead of a "5" for everything, so I'd love to hear more from them in an interview

Campus Involvement: Student Consulting for Nonprofit Organization, Tufaan Entertainment, Sigma Nu
Comments: Actually gave his Why Northwestern for his video, wasn't bad but didn't "wow" me. Says in one of his answers, "I’ve only been exposed to one small portion of what Northwestern has to offer" as to why he wants to learn more about NU, but there is a genuine passion evident through all of his answers, so I think it's worth giving him an interview

Campus Involvement: None
Comments: Undecided on major and not involved in anything on campus. Although the application answers are passionate and thoughtful, they just don't have much to go on.
